# Glitch monorepo boundaries

## Package map

- `apps/api` is the critical backend for licensing, webhooks, market data, and admin or internal operations.
- `apps/website` is the real public marketing surface.
- `apps/app` is placeholder scaffolding unless the user explicitly wants product work there.
- `ninjatrader/Glitch/AddOns/GlitchAddOn` and `ninjatrader/Glitch/Indicators/glitch` are the active NinjaTrader product.
- `ninjatrader/Glitch/Docs` is the current code-derived docs source.
- `ninjatrader/Glitch/Strategies` is research or legacy scope and stays out of default work unless explicitly requested.

## Shared rules

- Workspace files are the only source of truth.
- Keep changes package-scoped unless the task requires an explicit cross-package contract change.
- Read the owning README or NinjaTrader docs before editing instead of guessing.
- If a task mentions a docs app, note that `apps/docs` does not exist yet.
